                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Orissa manual for PSUs
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Bhubaneswar, Feb. 16: Chief minister Naveen Patnaik today released corporate governance manual for the state public sector undertakings  the first of its kind in the country.        
	The manual has been developed as part of the Orissa Public Enterprises Reform Programme, sponsored by the UK governments department for international development.        
	The manual prescribes compliance on the part of the state PSUs and the administrative departments, including signing MoUs between the two to ensure better functioning and accountability.        
	Releasing the manual, Naveen said Orissa was a leader in the field of public enterprise reforms. Highlighting the pivotal role of PSUs in the states economic growth and in providing public utility services, Naveen said: Since the state government has invested a huge amount of public resources in the PSUs, its necessary to make them effective for achieving social development and infrastructure objective as per their mandate.                                                                                                                                                           
